  "text": "\"Qualitative assessment of biofilm formation is the microorganisms are grown in agar with 5% sucrose and congo red\" [CITATION_1] . Positive results are indicated by black colonies with a dry crystalline consistency. When cultivated in a medium with high content of saccharides such as 10% sucrose solutions, with 5% congo red, strain L. plantarum Ts formed biofilm (Figure 1B) .",
